-- Market Chatter- Corporate finance press digest
-- 
-- Mon Jul 07, 2014 12:32AM EDT
-- None



July 7 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* Spanish telecoms company Telefonica <TEF.MC> is in talks to buy a stake in the Italian pay-TV business of Silvio Berlusconi's media group Mediaset <MS.MI>, two people familiar with the situation said on Saturday. [ID:nL6N0PG0HU]  * Private equity firm 3i Group Plc <III.L> is considering a sale or initial public offering of its Finish telecommunication unit, Eltel Networks, in a deal that may value it about 1 billion euros ($1.36 billion) including debt, Bloomberg reported on Sunday. [ID:nL4N0PH0E5]  * American Apparel Inc <APP.A> is in talks with Standard General, the New York-based hedge fund that controls 43 percent of the company's stock, to secure funding that would let the retailer pay off a $10 million loan and replace its board except for two co-chairmen, the Wall Street Journal reported on Sunday. [ID:nL2N0PH0HO]  * German airline Lufthansa's <LHAG.DE> new Chief Executive Carsten Spohr aims to sign a deal with Air China <601111.SS> during Chancellor Angela Merkel's state visit to Beijing this weekend, a German newspaper reported. [ID:nL6N0PG0C1]  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/] For the Morning News Call-EMEA newsletter click on [EMEA/MNC]